every breath, every heartbeat, every relationship, every dollar belongs to Him.

19:01.656 --> 19:02.218
So who are we?

19:03.340 --> 19:09.394
Well, the Bible gives us a word for who we are based on whose we are, and that is that we are stewards.

19:10.370 --> 19:14.595
A steward is someone that's like a manager who looks after something that belongs to another.

19:14.615 --> 19:19.101
So in a very real sense, everything you do in your entire life is an act of stewardship.

19:19.141 --> 19:25.689
How you treat your physical body, how you love your neighbor, how you spend your time, how you spend your money, how you spend your energy.

19:26.009 --> 19:28.132
Everything in your life is about stewardship.

19:28.152 --> 19:30.175
You are stewarding something that doesn't belong to you.

19:30.976 --> 19:36.082
And it should come as no surprise then that the Bible talks actually a ton about money.

19:36.354 --> 19:39.497
as sort of a barometer of us figuring that out in our lives.

19:39.577 --> 19:45.704
Because there's almost no greater barometer of our priorities than how we steward the money that God has given us.

19:46.805 --> 19:50.089
And a lot of times we look at our account and we're like, well, I earned this.

19:50.649 --> 19:51.190
Yes, you did.

19:51.230 --> 19:54.013
And God gave you the ability to earn what you earned.

19:55.234 --> 19:56.716
And every penny that you have is his.

19:56.736 --> 20:00.300
And so what are you doing with God's money?

20:00.340 --> 20:05.906
If you have a budget which I hope you do, you can see what's important to you.

20:06.946 --> 20:08.388
You can look at your budget.

20:08.848 --> 20:10.050
You can look at your calendar.

20:10.571 --> 20:13.775
You can look at how you spend your time and your week and your energy.

20:13.815 --> 20:17.179
And you can know who you think you are.

20:18.601 --> 20:21.084
There's a concept in the Bible that's called first fruits.

20:21.144 --> 20:24.789
And it basically reminds us that God should be our priority.

20:24.829 --> 20:26.131
He should get the first of everything.

20:26.791 --> 20:27.833
The first of our schedule.

20:28.894 --> 20:30.015
The first of our energy.

20:30.756 --> 20:32.018
The first of our time.

20:32.130 --> 20:37.846
the first of our money, that when Jesus is the first of everything, He gets the first before anything else.

20:38.207 --> 20:42.158
And then the rest of our life bends toward Him.

20:43.723 --> 20:46.290
But when something else always has the center

20:46.402 --> 20:47.944
everything will bend toward that.

20:47.964 --> 20:58.477
So what happens is, normally we think about whenever money kind of comes up into church, we get really awkward because we feel like God is just flipping the screen toward us and saying, I've got a few questions for you to answer here.

20:58.897 --> 21:02.422
And if you could just tap on the screen.

21:02.702 --> 21:04.584
And the problem is we feel that way.

21:04.604 --> 21:06.246
And it feels like angsty to us.

21:07.628 --> 21:10.752
But the big question is, what are our priorities?

21:12.034 --> 21:15.698
Are we giving to support gospel ministry, to take care of the poor?

21:16.386 --> 21:20.030
in our community, to be generous to those who are in need.

21:20.470 --> 21:22.913
It really betrays who is on the throne of our lives.

21:22.973 --> 21:23.634
We're stewards.

21:24.595 --> 21:25.516
We don't own ourselves.

21:27.338 --> 21:32.503
And so we as stewards and managers of everything God has, we can go now and look back to Jesus.

21:33.765 --> 21:35.967
Look at this in verse 22 and verse 23.

21:35.987 --> 21:42.354
It says, now all this took place to fulfill what was spoken by the Lord through the prophet

21:42.594 --> 21:47.665
See, the Virgin will become pregnant and give birth to a son, and they will name him a manual, which is translated.

21:47.766 --> 21:49.778
God is with us.

21:50.434 --> 21:57.424
And what Matthew is doing here is he's quoting the prophet Isaiah, and you'll notice that he gives Jesus another title, Immanuel.

21:57.784 --> 21:58.685
That right, Immanuel.

21:59.046 --> 21:59.967
And what does Immanuel mean?

21:59.987 --> 22:01.649
It means God is with us.

22:01.729 --> 22:04.273
And as we've seen in this series, Jesus has a lot of names.

22:04.313 --> 22:05.314
So is his name Jesus?

22:05.354 --> 22:05.595
Yes.

22:06.015 --> 22:07.077
Is his name Immanuel?

22:07.177 --> 22:07.497
Yes.

22:07.678 --> 22:10.161
Like he's got all these names, all these titles.

22:10.702 --> 22:16.790
And I love taking that name Jesus and putting it with that name Immanuel as it is in this passage.

22:17.891 --> 22:18.472
Think about this.

22:19.093 --> 22:19.794
Jesus.

22:20.770 --> 22:25.859
Emmanuel means the Lord who is with us, saves.

22:27.882 --> 22:30.647
There is so much that is packed into that.

22:30.667 --> 22:33.773
And I've been reflecting on that for the message.

22:33.813 --> 22:34.394
Think about this.

22:35.415 --> 22:40.925
Jesus came to save us, to be with us, to walk with us.

22:41.887 --> 22:43.690
Jesus was tempted as we are.

22:44.571 --> 22:46.194
He suffered as we do.

22:46.690 --> 22:51.074
He lived out his life under authority for the purpose of the Father.

22:51.154 --> 22:54.818
He knew who he was, so he knew who he was.

22:54.898 --> 22:56.860
He spent his whole life for others.

22:56.920 --> 22:58.281
He spent the whole thing.

22:58.822 --> 23:01.604
The arch of his life was bent toward that purpose.

23:03.246 --> 23:09.993
But now for a second, I want to go back to the person that we have already forgotten about because we know so little about him, Joseph.

23:11.334 --> 23:13.696
We've already kind of forgot we were talking about Joseph, didn't we?

23:14.857 --> 23:15.538
Joseph.

23:15.970 --> 23:17.801
is hearing all of this for the first time.

23:18.988 --> 23:22.066
I mean, he heard it from Mary, but now he hears it

23:22.178 --> 23:25.903
from this dream, and that has to be absolutely jarring for him.

23:26.244 --> 23:30.430
Because if Joseph marries Mary, he's inviting shame onto himself.

23:30.610 --> 23:36.699
Everyone in his small community would know that she was pregnant before they got married.

23:36.779 --> 23:43.128
And that doesn't carry a whole lot of shame in our culture today, but it does carry a lot in theirs.

23:43.248 --> 23:45.772
And so Joseph knew who he was.

23:47.374 --> 23:48.296
So he knew who he was.

23:49.457 --> 23:49.938
Look at this.

23:50.978 --> 23:54.302
When Joseph woke up, it's actually one of my favorite parts of that verse.

23:55.203 --> 23:56.584
But he got up, he's like, I am in.

23:57.665 --> 23:59.948
I would have got up and thought, was it the nachos, right?

24:00.709 --> 24:02.771
Like, he's like, nope, I'm in.

24:03.051 --> 24:12.121
When he got up, he did as the Lord's angel, it commanded him, he married her, but did not have sexual relations with her until they gave birth to a son, and he named him.

24:13.823 --> 24:20.210
He placed himself under the authority of God, and he named him Jesus.

24:21.730 --> 24:23.733
Think about what Joseph was doing in that moment.

24:24.835 --> 24:29.181
He gave up his right to direct his own life.

24:31.164 --> 24:38.955
In the words of one author, he discovered within himself the miraculous ability to obey the Word of God.

24:40.537 --> 24:44.864
Joseph ranked his stepson over himself.

24:46.466 --> 24:49.330
He took suffering and shame.

24:49.442 --> 24:51.005
the right to a good reputation.

24:51.065 --> 24:57.596
He and Mary had what a lot of people would have looked at as a dysfunctional little family.

24:59.098 --> 25:05.990
In fact, as I was reflecting on Joseph, it struck me that he pretty much disappears from the story shortly after this.

25:06.010 --> 25:07.693
He takes the family to Egypt.

25:07.953 --> 25:11.639
There's this encounter where they lose Jesus for a little bit and a whole thing.

25:11.659 --> 25:13.362
And then Joseph just kind of

25:13.506 --> 25:20.672
And most people believe that Joseph was older than Mary, that he probably died before Jesus grew up.

25:20.872 --> 25:26.117
And so what we know is that Joseph just wasn't around, so he wasn't there to see Jesus' ministry.

25:26.157 --> 25:28.399
He wasn't there to see Jesus' miracles.

25:28.419 --> 25:30.821
He didn't get to see his son walk on the water.

25:30.881 --> 25:33.964
He wasn't there when his son was nailed to the cross.

25:34.004 --> 25:36.286
And when he was buried, we know his mom was there, but Joseph wasn't there.

25:36.486 --> 25:37.647
He didn't see him get buried.

25:37.667 --> 25:39.649
He didn't get to see him raised from the dead.

25:39.689 --> 25:43.492
He didn't get to see him walk and talk and cook fish on the beach

25:43.472 --> 25:50.118
All the point everybody to God the Father, He didn't get to see His Son become Immanuel.

25:51.559 --> 25:53.441
He died before He saw the end of the story.

25:53.501 --> 25:56.123
He believed it, but He didn't see it.

25:56.524 --> 26:03.010
He closed His eyes one day in death and He opened them in glory to see His stepson.

26:03.430 --> 26:06.493
Jesus was the Savior, the Lord that had come to save.

26:08.394 --> 26:12.338
When I was a little kid, I won an award in VBS,

26:12.578 --> 26:14.020
Sunday school or one or something.

26:14.982 --> 26:24.918
And the award was this like cheap wooden frame that's made of plastic made to look like wood and had a piece of parchment made to look like parchment and had a Bible verse on it.

26:26.681 --> 26:34.514
And that piece of parchment in that Bible verse, it said, neither is there salvation in any other for there is.

26:35.458 --> 26:42.569
None other name given among men are given among men whereby we must be saved.

26:42.889 --> 26:50.941
Sorry, it's the King James Version and I'm just trying to picture the thing on my wall because night after night after night I looked at that as a little kid as I fell asleep.

26:52.443 --> 26:55.468
There is salvation in no one else but Jesus.

26:55.588 --> 26:55.908
Why?

26:56.870 --> 27:00.856
Because there is no other name under heaven that can save us.

27:02.038 --> 27:03.059
Only Jesus.

27:04.401 --> 27:05.042
Jesus

27:05.218 --> 27:06.259
is the one who is with us.

27:07.120 --> 27:08.982
Jesus is the one who saves.

27:09.002 --> 27:15.830
That baby that Joseph named Jesus grew up and he died on the cross for our sins.

27:16.831 --> 27:17.612
He was buried.

27:18.473 --> 27:19.354
He rose again.

27:19.374 --> 27:21.596
He ascended to right hand of God the Father.

27:22.658 --> 27:22.918
Why?

27:22.938 --> 27:27.743
For this is the will of my Father.

27:28.985 --> 27:33.650
That everyone who sees the Son and believes in Him will have eternal life

27:34.050 --> 27:37.314
and I will raise Him up on the last day.

27:38.776 --> 27:41.279
I don't know what your Christmas story is gonna be like.

27:42.140 --> 27:48.068
I don't know if you're the person who wakes up on Christmas morning and runs down and cannot wait to spend it with the family.

27:49.450 --> 27:54.076
Or if you've had such a dysfunctional family background that this is a season of pain.

27:55.618 --> 27:59.122
Maybe this is a season where it's a first time without a loved one.

28:01.026 --> 28:04.369
I don't know what your Christmas is gonna be like, but this is what I know is true.

28:05.511 --> 28:09.094
If you believe in Jesus, you will have eternal life.

28:10.636 --> 28:14.900
That he will raise you up on the last day to be with him.

28:14.920 --> 28:28.274
And he's gonna introduce you to his stepdad Joe and his mom Mary, a righteous dude, a poor young lady,

28:29.602 --> 28:32.125
who grew up to see her son go to the cross.

28:33.728 --> 28:36.472
And that's what this Christmas season is all about.

28:36.772 --> 28:39.035
So let's pray and then we'll continue.

28:39.796 --> 28:42.380
Heavenly Father, we thank You for Jesus.

28:43.021 --> 28:49.289
We thank You for that truth that all who believe in Him will have eternal life and they will be raised up on the last day.

28:49.830 --> 28:52.634
And so we confess that we believe in You.

28:54.196 --> 28:58.482
Maybe for some of us in this room, this is the first time we've ever even considered these things.

28:59.138 --> 29:05.114
And so I just pray that today would be the day that some people in this room would believe in Jesus for the first time.

29:06.357 --> 29:10.989
So that they will have eternal life and be raised up with him on the last day.

29:12.293 --> 29:14.398
We all pray this in Jesus' precious name.

29:15.501 --> 29:15.922
Amen.

